                            <h2>QMaths</h2>
                            <p>I started this project with the intention of creating a maths library that could handle all the necessary linear algebra for computer graphics.</p>
                            <p>Most maths libraries tend to use matrices to handle rotations but I decided it would work better with 
                            <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quaternion#:~:text=Hamilton%20defined%20a%20quaternion%20as,Multiplication%20of%20quaternions%20is%20noncommutative.">
                                quaternions</a> instead.</p>
                            <p>This library contains everything needed to handle translation, rotation and scaling, and allows vectors and matrices of any size.</p>
                            <p>The repo can be found <a href="https://github.com/shawrie777/QMaths">here.</a></p>
                        </div>
